# Website Utils RTL Physical Positioning

Applies when positioning overlays, floating CTAs, or fixed corners on website UI via `Box`/`Fixed`/`Row`/`Col` from `website/src/app/ui/base/components/Utils.tsx`.

## Rule

For **physical edge positioning** (which side of the viewport an element hugs), use Utils layout props:

- `l`, `r`, `t`, `b` (and spacing `pl`/`pr`/`ml`/`mr` where appropriate)

The website emotion/RTL pipeline mirrors these when `<html dir="rtl">`. Example: `r={"1rem"}` on `Fixed` places the element on the **right in LTR** and on the **left in RTL** automatically.

## Forbidden for layout positioning

- `baseCssStyle` objects branching on `myInstance.getRouter().isRTL` to pick `"left"` vs `"right"`.
- CSS logical properties invented ad hoc (`insetInlineStart`, `paddingInline`, etc.) when Utils props already express the intent.
- Dynamic prop keys like `[isRTL ? "right" : "left"]: "1rem"`.

## Allowed uses of `isRTL`

- Behaviors CSS/props cannot express alone: drawer slide-in side (`CustomerDrawer`), breadcrumb separator icon direction (`Breadcrumb`), bottom-bar nav alignment — see `website-route-reactive-components.mdc`.

## Canonical case (floating mobile CTA)

Floating action chip pinned to the viewport edge:

```tsx
<Fixed r={"1rem"} b={`calc(${Dims.bottomBarHeight} + 1.25rem)`} z={zIndex.modals}>
```

Do not replace with `isRTL` ternaries or `left`/`right` in `baseCssStyle`.

## Authority

- `website/src/app/ui/base/components/Utils.tsx` (`l`/`r` layout props)
- `.cursor/rules/website-icon-rtl-flip.mdc` (directional **icons** — separate concern from edge positioning)
